caption: Best food, friendly staff, regularly excellent mood. They charge affordable pricing and the food quality is awesome. Highly recommended.
Fantastic and tasty food, I like the character the spot has, and the employees were very kind. I will surely come back.
I go here all the time, it's good. But I got shafted with the portions of vegies. Kind of outrageous. They wanted more money. Kinda disappointed.
Great fresh fish, excellent side toppings (spring for the tobiko) and delicious sauces. Can't say enough good about this place. Just wish they had Lipton pureleafs.
Cashier is incredibly rude!
favorite spot around this part of town for quality lunch. seafood and ingredients are fresh and delicious. staff is usually friendly. not a lot of space for seating but just enough.

Omg, I have been craving a Poke bowl for months and today my sister treated me to Kome Waza and it was amazing. The seafood is fresh and the ginger sauce was delicious. I will definitely be back soon! Wish they were near my job uptown.
One of the best poke bowls ever had, will be back for more
This place is the truth, great quality food, and clean eating area.
One of the best poke in the USA. 5 star for huge selection of ingredients and japanese influence flavor. So fresh!

My favorite poke for work lunch.  I missed the "spicy" designation on my first bowl and that was painful, but still delicious.  Just keep in mind if they call it spicy, they mean business.  I like that the ingredients are better than your average poke spot.
A great lunch spot!
Delicious poke bowls.  Fresh ingredients, wonderful sushi rice, tasty flavors.  Modest portions.
OK only
(Translated by Google) good prices  (Original) Buenos precios

First time back in a while. Quality, service, and overall experience has started going down recently. Still not a bad place, just not what it once was. Probably not going to be returning any time soon which is sad since I used to come at least once a week for lunch.
Service and quality are getting worse.  Staff is rude.
Got the tuna bowl with brown rice, seaweed, lettuce, sesame seeds and a few more things. It was delicious. The space is not terribly large but the service is fast and efficient. Definitely try it.

I went in with high expectations so this may have affected my score.  One of the server's was curt and grouchy, but down the line the other servers were cheery and helpful.  The fish was reasonably fresh and they had roe which isnt always the case with poke but I find makes a big difference. The spicy sauce was whatever. I also ordered a pork bun which was very underwhelming...Sauce was overpowering and the bun didn't have the right texture.  Probably wouldn't come back...
I prefer other places in the area but it was pretty good!
Fresh fish, poke with a different spin - sauces are interesting. Like that there’s unlimited toppings!
Go-to poke lunch spot, best in the area.
this is the best poke in the city, hands down. the fish is always fresh and the avocado cream sauce is to die for!!!

The portions are fairly small for the price. The preset bowls are also not very well thought out in my opinion - it’s much better to create your own. There is also not too much sitting space in the shop.
I'm glad Kome Waza opened a spot on 1st Ave between 68th and 69th street! Awesome food.
Clean, fresh fish, good portions for $11. Try the matcha ice cream
Really good for the price! I'll take my bowl to Elevated Acre for a nice lunch and then come back for their green tea soft serve <3

I have been coming here for a year. At first it was good, high quality food. However their portions just keep shrinking every time i come back, and their “bowl” is basically a snack item rather than being enough for a meal. In addition, when I ask for toppings, they always give you just the tiniest possible amount and are very stingy now. It’s really disappointing, as I had enjoyed this place previously.

Really fresh ingredients! As a vegetarian I felt there were ample options that made my poke experience here much better than other places. I recommend trying couple of their sauces. Those were the stars for me!

Best poke ball place that I know so far. I am Japanese and I am picky with raw fish. They have the freshest fish here and the ingredients are all great. Another reason I like about this place is that they have just the regular soy sauce to mix in. I like to use just soy sauce so it won't  overkill the flavor of fish and veggies. My favorite mix of poke ball is, sushi rice + yellow tale + salmon + cucumber + radish sprouts + nori + ikura + soy sauce. Highly recommended!
Seriously my favorite Poke spot of all the ones I've tried in the city.  It may have to do with the level of care they have for the food, which you can taste.
Decent poke for a quick to go lunch in FiDi.
Excellent poke with lots of options I haven't seen elsewhere in New York like their salted mango cream and white soy avocado sauces.
As usual, another amazing lunch.
Delicious and fresh - a bit pricey with add-ons but a great occasional treat.

Really great lunch spot. The food is high quality and not that expensive for the area, definitely the best poke in the neighborhood. Lines tend to be long here, sometimes going out the door. It's best to order online and pick up.
Great lunch!
Really Really bad. Rotten hamachi to point it smelled. Stay away seriously. I am hoping I don't get sick. WARNING!
Very pricey for the portion size but food is fresh.

Update: I will give this place another try, hopefully the manager hired better staffing or provided proper training to the staff.  Worst place ever. Whoever has rated this place as 5 stars or anything above 3 star, had NEVER ate real poke before.  Service alone I critique it at 0/5. The server gave me 2 pieces of shrimp for a selection of meat topping. TWO. I don't that should be acceptable anywhere for the amount I pay.  Food: not fresh. Shrimp tasted frozen. 1/5.
The best poke bowl I have ever had. This is my highlight in all of new York!!!
It's fast, no need to wait, good for a quick bite and the seafood is fresh as well.
fresh and good sushi bowls, long lines
Not the best food I've had.
I like what I eat. It eas fresh and delicious.
Excellent food and the price is very doable!
SUPER FRESH INGREDIENTS

Food was fresh and delicious. Everything I tried was very good. Pricey but definitely worth the treat. Place is small but clean and there area few tables to sit and eat. Staff is friendly and fast service

If you are comparing poke places in FiDi this is your best one. Place is very clean (but small), staff is professional, and food is a cut above the standard spices mayo and tuna you find at other places  They strive for a bit more authenticity and natural subtle flavors. They even make their own teas and Onigiri. Yum!
Slightly expensive but incredibly delicious. Some of the best food in the Fidi area.
Great little spot...love the wasabi cashew sause...

The Poke bowl was ok. The counter staff was quite friendly. I thought the food was rather pricey for the portion size. I ordered their signature, White Soy Avocado Cream Bowl, but wasn't really blown away.
Good poke. Very crowded during lunch time.
Great first experience!  All the mix in options are great, and I didn't feel shorted on any of the items I selected.  Delicious and fresh.

Second poke shop to open down here in a matter of months. Location is pretty small but clean and there's some room to sit. Overall pretty good but wasn't blown away. The ingredients seemed fresh but it felt like the fish had an overly fishy taste.
Great lunch spot, think of a burrito bowl, expect instead of Mexican cuisine, Sushi. Very flavorful!
Very good. Amazing green tea ice cream too !
